The items below are merely inspirational. This annex must be accurately and exhaustively worded by the project manager.
Operational incidents
A category A incident means an incident in an operating environment if, for example:
user cannot log into the Application
when the app repeatedly falls on the same step and the user cannot complete the critical process
when the system shows too long (double the defined performance parameters)
user activity responses
when it is not possible to print documentation or report for the client
when the end customer is shown incorrect data
Critical functionality/processes Applications are:
account opening or closing
daily shutter
A category B incident means an incident in an operating environment if, for example:
the user's work is slowed down, but it doesn't have a serious impact on the workflow
when non-critical functionality is unavailable to the end customer.
A Category C incident means an incident in an operating environment if, for example:
when it's a language flaw, or a font other than an agreed font
when it's a graphics error in the user interface that doesn't confuse the user's use of the interface
when a Documentation defect is involved
Incidents from Acceptance Environment
A category TA incident means an Incident in an Acceptance Environment if by example:
it is not possible to base a client on a system
The TB category incident means an Incident in an Acceptance Environment if, for example:
Could Not Change Client Account Unchecked Parameter
Incident of category TC means Incident in an Acceptance Environment if, for example:
when it's a language flaw, or a font other than an agreed font
when it's a graphics error in the user interface that doesn't confuse the user's use of the interface
when a Documentation defect is involved
