Annex 12 / Safety rules
1. Definitions of terms
1.1. For the purposes of this Annex, the following terms and phrases have the meanings specified below:
A security incident means any breach of the confidentiality, integrity or availability of Information Assets.
An information asset means any information, processes, hardware or software components that (1) support the business activities of the Entity, or (2) have value to the Entity, or (3) whose disclosure, unauthorized change or unavailability has a negative impact on the Entity.
Persons The contractor means persons directly or indirectly involved in the performance of the object of this Treaty, including persons subcontracted by the contractor.
Authorised entity environment means premises in which the Authorised Entity carries out its business activities and information-communication systems used by the Authorised Entity that contain Information Assets.
2. Personnel security
2.1 None of the Persons of the Zhotovitele:
2.1.1. has no criminal record;
2.1.2 has not previously been convicted of an intentional offence and is not being prosecuted at the time of fulfilling the subject matter of this Treaty,
2.2. If the contractor finds a non-compliance with the above rules in the Persons of the contractor, he must inform the contractor of this without delay. The principal is entitled to require that such a person no longer participate in the execution of the works arising from the subject-matter of this Treaty, either directly or indirectly, and is entitled to require the Contractor to provide adequate compensation.
2.3 The contractor provides the Orderer with a full name list of the Persons of the Contractor. The contractor undertakes to inform the Client of changes in the personnel arrangements for the performance of this contract in advance.
2.4. Persons The contractor:
2.4.1 must be familiar with these safety rules,
2.4.2 have all the necessary examinations and attestations that result from the law or regulator's requirements as to the type of work to be carried out in connection with the fulfilment of this Treaty,
2.4.3 The contractor is a regular educator in the areas of information security.
2.5. Persons of the Authorised Body shall not enter the environment under the influence of addictive, narcotic or psychotropic substances or bring weapons, explosives, accelerants, warfare agents, poisons, radioactive and toxic substances or any other substance endangering human life and/or health.
3. Physical security
3.1. Access Persons of a contractor to the Entity's environment shall be permitted only if their presence is necessary for the performance of the employment obligations arising from this Treaty.
3.2 Persons The contractor in the Authorised Entity Environment is always accompanied by the Responsible Officer of the Client.
3.3 Free movement Persons of the Authorised Person in the Authorised Person Environment are only permitted if a personal access card has been issued to the person. The contractor may not further lend the access card to third parties or allow third parties access to the Authorised Entity's environment.
3.4 In case of loss of the access card or in case of suspected loss of the access card, the Contractor is obliged to inform the Orderer without delay.
3.5. Without undue delay after the completion of work under this Treaty, or after the termination of this Treaty, or if further physical access is no longer required Persons of the Zhotovitele to the Authorised Entity Environment, The Client shall ensure that all Persons of the Zhotovitele return the Lent Access Card to the Client.
3.6. Without the prior written consent of the Client Person The contractor may not remove any Information Assets from the Authorised Entity Environment via a storage medium.
4. Identification and Authentication Persons The contractor in the Authorised Entity Environment
4.1. Persons Only accounts allowing the user to be identified unambiguously and with only such authorisations as are strictly necessary for the performance of their employment obligations under this Treaty shall be allocated to the contractor.
4.2 Normal operations are performed by the contractor under non-privileged accounts, using accounts with admin privileges only when necessary.
4.3 Persons A contractor may not access the Internet if it works under an account with administrator privileges or with applications running under administrator privileges.
4.4 Inactive accounts Persons The contractors are proactively reported by the contractors.
4.5 Shared accounts are only used by the Contractor with the prior written consent of the Client.
4.6 In the event of a password being divulged or a password being suspected, the Composer must ensure that the password is changed or blocked without delay.
5. Certificate loading
5.1 Access to certificates (both logical and physical) will be granted only to those Persons of the Zhotovitele for whom such access is necessary for the performance of their professional duties.
5.2. Without the written consent of the Client Persons The contractor may not provide the certificates or make them available to third parties.
5.3 Once installed, certificates may only be stored in secure storage in the places where they are required for compliance with this Treaty, and any other copies shall be destroyed in such a way as to make it impossible to renew them.
5.4 If possible, the certificate's private key must be set as not exportable. The certificate's private key must always be protected by a strong password and not stored in an unencrypted form.
5.5 The contractor undertakes to inform the Client immediately of the loss or suspected loss of confidentiality of the private key of the certificate.
6. Handling of Information Assets
6.1 Working with Information Assets is limited to locations that exclude the observation of sensitive information by unauthorised persons. Specifically, it is forbidden to work with Information Assets in mass transit vehicles, public places and places where there is a risk of being spotted by industrial cameras.
6.2 After completion of the work under this Treaty, the contractor shall without undue delay return or remove all Information Assets stored in the environment of the Zhotovitele, unless the possession of such information is required by the laws of the Czech Republic. This applies to both electronic and paper documentation. The removal of Information Assets must be done in a way that makes it impossible to reinstate them.
6.3 The Contractor may not grant access to the Information Assets to any third parties not entitled to participate in the performance of this Treaty without the prior written consent of the Contractor.
6.4 The contractor is required to ensure adequate security of the computing equipment on or through which the Information Assets are stored, processed or transmitted. In the context of Information Assets, the Zhotovitel will ensure that in the environment of the Zhotovitele:
6.4.1 encryption tools are used to encrypt disks, folders, or files to prevent unauthorized access to Information Assets,
6.4.2 malicious code detection and removal tools are used with the setting of a periodic update of the malicious code signature database with a frequency not exceeding one week, and appropriate surveillance, logging and response processes are set up for a malicious code hit,
6.4.3 defines, configures, executes and monitors the process of updating the security patches of software components at an interval not exceeding one month from the release of the patches,
6.4.4, the Internet environment is separated by a firewall that is connected to surveillance, and Remote Access Zhotovitele Persons uses exclusively encrypted VPN connections to prevent unauthorized interception and alteration of transmitted communications.
6.5. If Information Assets are transferred by the Competent Body away from the premises of the Authorised Entity, the Competent Body is required to take due care of the physical security of these Assets and to keep these Information Assets under surveillance at all times. The contractor shall comply with the safety and operational instructions of the hardware manufacturer on which the Information Assets are processed.
7. Work in the Entity Environment
7.1 The contractor is required to acquaint himself with and act in accordance with the Standard of Classification of Information Assets if the Client provides it.
7.2. For hardware that is owned and managed by the Client, or hardware that, including its configuration, has been approved in advance by the Client, the Contractor may not make unapproved changes to the configuration of this hardware by the Client. In particular, the Zhotovitel must not make changes to the hardware security configuration. The security patch application process, including responsibilities arising from the roles within the process, must be explicitly and formally established for each piece of hardware so installed.
7.3 Without the prior written consent of the Client, the Contractor shall not install or run any, pre-approved software by the Client.
7.4. Without the written consent of the Procurer, the Procurer is not entitled to carry out any physical or logical security testing or any type of control mechanisms of the Authorised Body.
7.5 The contractor must not tamper with audit records in any way.
7.6 Persons The contractors are not authorised to work with software, hardware or data content not directly related to the fulfilment of this Treaty.
7.7. Persons The contractor may not engage in any activities detrimental to other natural or legal persons, including sending unsolicited emails, sending fraudulent emails, distributing malicious code or engaging in attacks to disable the availability of services.
7.8 All steps taken by Persons of the Contractor The Contractor logs and keeps a record of them for 3 years.
7.9. Without the written consent of the Orderer, Persons of the Zhotovitele may not connect their own storage devices to any of the authorized entity's computer equipment.
7.10. In the post provided, the Persons of the Zhotovitele are obliged to provide for the time of physical absence:
7.10.1. cleanliness and order so that the work site can be safely used;
7.10.2 Adequate physical security of all Information Assets;
7.10.3 Logically locking access to Information Assets so that unauthorized access to these Information Assets cannot occur.
7.11. Persons of the contractor are not authorised to install a device enabling remote interception or to take any audio or video recording without the prior written consent of the contractor.
8. Crisis management
8.1. Persons The contractors are required to prevent, as far as possible, the occurrence of crisis situations (e.g. fire, explosion, flood, etc.) and situations where injuries to persons or property damage to the beneficiary could occur.
8.2 In the event of an emergency situation, a Person of the Zhotovitele who is physically present at the place of the event shall, without exception and delay, comply with the regulations and directives in force at the location and obey the instructions for evacuation and protection of persons. This also applies to exercise.
8.3 In the event of crisis management, the Person of the Zhotovitele is obliged to follow the instructions of the Client's crisis manager without delay.
9. Security incident reports
9.1 If the Zhotovitel identifies a security incident, it is required to report it promptly to the https://helpdesk.jtfg.com tool (phone: +420 221 710 911).
